different city and they will bring to 17 the number of screens 
showing the movie 
the openings were expected by this weekend in detroit austin 
texas houston santa ana calif san diego phoenix ariz 
tucson ariz and philadelphia 
last weekend the movie played to soldout crowds in seven us 
cities and two in canada earning 401211 a 44579 perscreen 
average 
five of the theaters taking on the last temptation of christ 
for this weekend are owned by american multicinema previously 
movie chains such as general cinema theaters edwards cinemas and 
luxury theaters all said they would not show the film 
last week an estimated crowd of 25000 protesters gathered 
outside universal studios to protest the film based on a novel of 
the same name by nikos kazantzakis and directed by martin scorsese 
demonstrators also marched and handed out leaflets to moviegoers at 
theaters showing the film 
the protesters consider the movie sacrilegious particularly a 
