president mohammed zia ulhaq who guided 
pakistan for 11 years enjoyed close ties with the united states 
despite liabilities that would have doomed that relationship had he 
governed a less strategically important country 
zias refusal to be intimidated by the presence of over 100000 
soviet troops in neighboring afghanistan overrode all other 
considerations in washington enabling pakistan to be among the 
largest recipients of american assistance 
zia who died wednesday in a plane crash along with us 
ambassador arnold l raphel and an american brigadier general 
allowed usbacked afghan rebels to use pakistan as a staging 
ground for attacks on afghanistan he also permitted pakistan to be 
used as a safe haven for 3 million afghan refugees 
