the national weather service says areas 
throughout the united states hit by drought high heat or the 
threat of forest fires will continue to suffer 
the services 30day forecast for midaugust to midseptember 
released wednesday said the dakotas nebraska iowa and the 
western great lakes area the farming heartland already withered by 
drought will continue to be dry 
the same area and the eastern region from north carolina to 
maine also are expected to continue to endure higherthannormal 
temperatures while the risk of forest fires will continue high in 
the timberlands from minnesota west to washington and south through 
california the weather service said it warned that the risk will 
be extreme for parts of wymoning montana idaho oregon 
nevada and california 
higher than normal rainfall is predicted for the texaslouisiana 
gulf coast and for the southeast from florida to north carolina 
the weather service said 
</TEXT>
