<TEXT>
soprano angelina reaux confidently mixes acting 
with singing kurt weill songs in stranger here myself now 
running at the offbroadway susan stein shiva theater in the public 
theater complex 
her fullbodied operatic voice is sure and attractive and her 
acting isnt overdone her show is effective to a degree but isnt 
a completely rewarding evening of theater the ingredient thats 
missing is the ability to convey the emotion of the songs through 
the sound of her voice 
the stage is set as a hotel room with a few small tables lamps 
a chair and a red spread on the bed miss reaux wears a black 
dress has a small battered suitcase she sings one song after 
another not making a story line but acting each of them 
in the barbara song from the threepenny opera when she 
recounts saying no to men but not saying no to macheath she lies 
on the bed and grabs the headboard as though shes in bondage 
in the title song im a stranger here myself with its 
catchy melody and lyrics by ogden nash from one touch of 
venus shes tipsy while really delivering the song the next 
surabaya johnny has her whimpering reaching toward a bottle 
of pills apparently considering suicide then she lightens the 
mood again with foolish heart also from one touch of venus 
her operatic voice is perfect for lonely house from street 
scene but lowdown irony is needed for solomon song from 
threepenny opera and miss reaux doesnt deliver it 
there are survivors in kurt weill songs theres tragedy 
heartbreak abuse hopeless love daydreams of ships coming in and 
rescuing a life theyre greatly to be enjoyed by people who like 
strong songs instead of wimpy ones theyre enjoyed less by people 
who prefer upbeat sentiments and situations 
miss reaux has sung a great deal for conductor leonard 
bernstein which is a strong recommendation her show which had 
three instrumentalists was directed by christopher alden 
however anybody who has heard teresa stratas also an opera 
singer sing weill knows that she can be bawdy despairing 
misguided hardhearted or swaggeringly stoical just through the 
sound of her voice that has a stronger impact that miss reaux 
singing as she acts out the songs sentiments 
