the question of the authenticity of the score a wind band 
arrangement titled harmoniemusik which is part of mozarks 
opera the abduction from the seraglio along with that of 
other scores found periodically remain the topic of scholarly 
debate 
the piece was discovered last year in west germany by bastiaan 
blonhert a dutch musicologist 
in a letter to his father dated july 20 1782 mozart wrote that 
he hoped to complete a wind arrangement of the opera quickly or 
else someone will step in front of me and reap the profit 
whether he actually completed the work is not known however 
musicologist hc robbins landon said that a newspaper article 
written in august 1782 advertises a wind band performance of the 
work noting that tickets are available from the lemonade seller 
at the new market 
the copy found in west germany is not in mozarts handwriting 
nor is it in the handwriting of any of the copyists mozart was 
known to employ 
