thai waters and thailands fishing fleet the worlds largest 
often is caught poaching in the waters of neighboring countries 
securing the release of fishermen in communist vietnam has been 
difficult because of the strained relations between the two 
countries thailand backs guerrillas fighting the decadelong 
vietnamese military occupation of cambodia 
a thai foreign ministry official who requested anonymity said 
vietnamese authorities repatriated 10 thai fishermen on aug 12 
after the thai government paid 5000 in fines 
the fishermen were captured oct 17 following a shootout in 
which two thais were killed the vietnamese government reduced the 
fine by half because of the two deaths the official said 
