a small earthquake an aftershock of a series 
of quakes on sunday was felt thursday in central utah but there 
were no reports of damage or injury 
the magnitude of the 644 am quake was 46 on the richter 
scale said jim pechmann a seismologist at the university of 
utahs seismograph stations 
a second tremor 10 magnitude was recorded in the same area at 
656 am the university said 
the carbon county sheriffs office said it received numerous 
calls and there were reports of the temblor being felt in emery 
and sanpete counties 
on sunday central utah and western colorado were rocked by 
three quakes the largest of which was about 56 on the richter 
scale of ground motion and caused some minor damage about a dozen 
aftershocks followed monday 
the tremors occurred in an area where there had been no known 
faults 
the epicenter of thursdays temblor was believed to be in 
approximately the same area as sundays about 34 miles south of 
price and 14 miles east of ferron pechmann said 
it was an aftershock of sundays quakes he said seismologists 
had said aftershocks could continue through midweek 
an aftershock of this size is not considered unusual given the 
size of last sundays main shock pechmann said 
every increase of one number on the richter scale means a 
tenfold increase in magnitude 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale can cause slight 
damage in the local area 4 moderate damage 5 considerable damage 
6 severe damage a 7 reading is a major earthquake capable of 
widespread heavy damage 8 is a great quake capable of 
tremendous damage 
