the effectiveness of last winters influenza 
vaccine may have been reduced by a midseason drift in the 
predominant flu virus federal health researchers concluded in a 
report on the 198788 season 
health officials reported late last year that the predominant 
strain of flu ah3n2 one of the three major flu types appeared 
to be drifting or changing into a somewhat different form 
because these variations were not recognized until the fall of 
1987 the influenza vaccine which contains vaccine against all 
three major types could not be modified to include the new 
variant the national centers for disease control said thursday 
in its weekly report 
as a result the efficacy of the vaccine at least in certain 
highrisk persons may have been reduced the agency concluded 
cdc officials earlier this spring said the recommended 198889 
flu vaccine should contain a new formula to better protect against 
the new ah3n2 strain known as the sichuan flu 
