<TEXT>
chinese leader zhao ziyang said the politburo was 
working on a fiveyear economic plan that would allow staterun 
enterprises more autonomy but he added that inflation threatens 
reform news reports said wednesday 
zhao general secretary of the communist party also said the 
first chinesesoviet summit meeting in three decades is possible if 
moscow first urges vietnam to withdraw its troops from cambodia 
the statement represented a softening of previous chinese stances 
vietnam has announced plans to withdraw 50000 troops half of 
its force from cambodia by the end of the year and the rest by 
early 1990 
zhaos remarks came tuesday in an interview with shinji sakai 
president of japans kyodo news service at the coastal resort of 
beidaihe they were reported wednesday by kyodo staff members who 
attended and the official chinese xinhua news agency 
zhao a leading proponent of economic reform with senior leader 
deng xiaoping said the politburo was convened monday to discuss 
the comprehensive fiveyear program the politburo is chinas 
highest decisionmaking body 
the general secretary said the package would be adopted in 
principle by the politburo and could be put into effect starting at 
the beginning of next year 
zhao said the government will give priority to reform of 
staterun enterprises giving them more independence and making 
them liable for losses the key to better efficiency lies in making 
all enterprises compete for markets promoting the better ones and 
eliminating the inferior ones he said 
chinas staterun enterprises operate under the control of local 
party officials and central planners the nations private 
enterprises already enjoy a large measure of autonomy 
zhao also told the japanese that price reform another key goal 
cannot succeed unless the economy becomes more efficient 
the government is moving to lift price controls and let prices 
be determined by market value but producers cannot keep up with 
rising demand he said the problem helped push consumer inflation 
rates to near 20 percent in the first half of the year 
whether we can in the course of reform check excessive price 
rises will be the deciding factor in whether the reform program for 
the next year is carried out smoothly zhao said sharp 
inflation could erode peoples confidence in economic reform 
the government raised interest rates on loans and savings 
accounts tuesday in an effort to discourage capital investment and 
encourage personal savings state banks have also announced they 
will curtail loans to cool off the economy which grew at an 
excessively rapid pace of 11 percent in the first half of the year 
zhao denied reports in the foreign press that the annual summer 
policy meetings at the beidaihe resort broke down in late july 
