watch wtnh in new haven conn and youll get the story ahead 
of everyone else the announcer explains especially the story just 
shown it never happened 
across the continent in los angeles viewers of knbc see news 
anchorman john beard and anchorwoman linda alvarez share a fan 
letter the fan says beard deserves a hug and a there there 
pat when hes telling folks bad news 
then beard reads a compliment for ducking under his desk during 
the oct 2 earthquake wrong anchorman that was morning news 
anchorman kent shocknekyo kent mail call beard says 
rapping the desk top 
promotions for television news shows cute coy or concocted 
have slipped out of the narrow restrictions that once dictated that 
such spots feature only the depth and capability of the news team 
the new generation of commercials are forged from years of 
behindthescenes wars between news and promotion departments did 
one side win 
i would say its kind of a meeting of the minds said jay 
curtis member services manager of the broadcast promotion amp 
marketing executives the advertisements are taking the content 
of news and fitting it into the form of promotion 
curtis estimated that concocted news events were featured in 20 
percent of the 600 news promotions the bpme received recently for 
its gold medallion awards 
although the scenario for the wtnh commercial was not based on 
a specific event it was indicative of things that happen at 
hospitals said wtnh promotion manager donald cohen he said 
there had been no negative comments from the public or journalists 
about the spot 
wtnh an abc affilliate has been running a neckandneck 
ratings war with wfsb the hartfordbased cbs affiliate cohen said 
i find that promotion directors use as a litmus test for 
themselves whether they can make their news no 1 curtis said 
adding that the tighter the market the tougher the promotion 
campaign when the news gets the numbers everything else falls 
into place 
they were a pretty boring station when they hired me said 
former knbc promotion manager vince manze now an executive vice 
president with steve sohmer inc my mandate was to put some life 
in the station the network had taken off the local station had 
not he said 
cohen said he was prepared for criticism of the wtnh commercial 
i was ready to explain the thinking that went behind the spot 
and we were prepared to put the word dramatization over it 
but cohen said the viewers of wtnh were sophisticated enough to 
understand the commercial was not a real event 
but we wanted to make sure we were doing something that was 
actually related to covering the news he said 
the commercial for knbc was one of several spots devised by 
chuck blore and don richman inc that involves oncamera reporters 
the first series of ads featured weather reporter fritz coleman 
