<TEXT>
anheuserbusch cos inc said thursday it will 
begin marketing its new michelob dry beer in five markets sept 1 
in the first phase of a national rollout 
the nations biggest brewer said the superpremium brand will be 
introduced simultaneously in fresno and santa barbara calif 
houston tallahassee fla and dayton ohio 
dry beer is less sweet and has less of an aftertaste than 
regular beer it has become a sensation in the japanese beer 
market where it was first developed 
dry beer in japan has a higher alcohol content than regular 
beer but anheuserbusch said its dry beer alcohol content would be 
approximately 5 percent of volume the level of american beers set 
by federal law 
</TEXT>
