<TEXT>
assets of the nations 447 money market mutual 
funds rose by 3 billion in the latest week the investment company 
institute said thursday 
the rise to 26856 billion in the sevenday period ended 
wednesday followed a revised 8465 million rise in the funds 
assets the previous week according to the washingtonbased mutual 
fund trade group the increase originally was reported as 8403 
million 
the investment company institute said that in the latest week 
assets of 221 general purpose funds rose 166 billion to 8536 
billion a record high amount for that category 
assets of 101 brokerdealer funds increased by 7706 million to 
11398 billion and assets of 125 institutional funds rose 5753 
million to 6922 billion the institute reported 
jacob dreyer the institutes chief economist attributed the 
increases largely to the growing attractiveness of yields on money 
market funds vs yields on moneymarket accounts and shortterm 
certificates of deposit 
the sevenday average yield on money market mutual funds rose in 
the week ended tuesday to 714 percent from 698 percent the 
previous week according to donoghues money fund report a trade 
journal based in holliston mass 
the 30day average yield rose to 699 percent from 690 percent 
donoghues said 
the average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was 
34 days unchanged from the previous week donoghues said 
the newsletter bank rate monitor said its survey of 100 leading 
commercial banks savings and loan assocations and savings banks in 
the nations 10 largest markets showed the effective annual yield 
available on money market accounts rose to 587 percent as of 
wednesday from 583 percent a week earlier 
the north palm beach flabased newsletter said the effective 
annual yield available on special savings accounts called super 
now accounts was 513 percent unchanged 
bank rate monitor said the effective annual yield was 751 
percent on sixmonth certificates of deposit up from 742 the 
previous week yields were 782 percent on 1year cds up from 772 
percent 812 percent on 2year cds up from 804 percent and 
845 percent on 5year cds up from 840 percent 
</TEXT>
