the us dollar recovered slightly from a lower 
opening against the japanese yen on friday while share prices 
edged higher in quiet trading on the tokyo stock exchange 
the dollar opened at 13323 yen down 070 yen from the previous 
days close and traded sluggishly throughout the morning the 
currency was changing hands at 13343 yen by late morning 
there is a strong waitandsee mood in the market said one 
foreign exchange dealer speaking on condition of anonymity 
in the stock market the widelywatched nikkei stock average of 
225 selected issues rose 4496 to 2817432 points by the morning 
close 
a stock dealer in tokyo who asked not to be identified said 
the market was slow because it had no clear no direction at the 
moment 
its just a few stocks that are getting picked up and 
pushed he said 
